The paper proposes a framework for autonomous navigation in row-crop fields using on-board cameras without the need for explicit localization or maintaining a map of the field. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper heavily relies on computer vision techniques for image processing and analysis, which suggests that it could also belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques for training the navigation system, which suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with the control and coordination of multiple subsystems in the robot, which suggests that it could also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
